Segmentation of the plastic compounding market based on product, polymer, and application provides valuable insights into the industry dynamics. Thermoplastic compounding and thermosetting compounding are the two primary product segments, with thermoplastic compounds dominating the market due to their versatility and recyclability. In terms of polymers, polypropylene (PP) holds a significant market share, followed by polyethylene (PE), polyvinyl chloride (PVC), polystyrene (PS), polyethylene terephthalate (PET), and other polymer types. The application segment highlights key sectors driving demand for plastic compounds, including automotive, electrical & electronics, packaging, construction, consumer goods, and others.

